    "updated_at": "2015-12-16T00:36:46Z",
    "body": "@zcbenz Tried it with type set to textured, but still get the issue. **Note: Frame set to true or false have can reproduce this issue. (The only difference is traffic lights appear on hover for frame.)**\n\nThis is the code to reproduce:\n\n```\napp.on('ready', function() {\n  mainWindow = new BrowserWindow({\n    'width': 800,\n    'height': 600,\n    'autoHideMenuBar': true,\n    'useContentSize': true,\n    'titleBarStyle': 'hidden-inset',\n    'frame': false, // can be either true or false to reproduce issue\n    'fullscreen': true,\n    'type': 'textured'\n  });\n  mainWindow.loadURL('file://' + __dirname + '/index.html');\n  mainWindow.focus();\n});\n```\n"
